      "question_id": 79807926,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>SSM does not guarantee declaration order for transitions that share the same source state and event, especially when they all have guard conditions. The framework processes the transition definitions and stores them in internal collections (like Set or Map), which often don't preserve the insertion order you used in the builder configuration.\nYou could use different priority for builders</p>\n<pre><code>builder.configureTransitions()\n    .withExternal()\n        .source(&quot;D&quot;).target(&quot;D+&quot;)\n        .event(&quot;!&quot;)\n        .priority(10) // Set a high priority to ensure it's checked first\n        .guard(ctx -&gt; {\n            System.out.println(&quot;evaluating DATE...&quot;);\n            return &quot;tomorrow&quot;.equals(ctx.getMessage().getHeaders().get(&quot;event&quot;));\n        });\n</code></pre>\n",
